@using Northwind.Models
@model IEnumerable<Product>

<!-- Add icon library -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">

<style>
    .checked {
        color: #0b86de;
    }
</style>

<body>

    <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto p-3 py-md-5">


        <h1>Product Name</h1>

        <div><span class="fa fa-star checked"></span><span class="fa fa-star checked"></span><span
                class="fa fa-star checked"></span><span class="fa fa-star"></span><span class="fa fa-star"></span> - 2
            ratings </div>
        <p>Price: $00.00</p>
        
        @foreach (var item in Model)
            {
            <p> @item.ProductName </p>
            } 
        
        @* instead of doing a  *@


        <div class="mb-5">
            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg px-2">Add to Cart</a>
        </div>

        <hr>

        <div class="row g-5">
            <h3 class="my-4 ">Customer Reviews Of Product Name</h3>

            <div class="card mb-4 border-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <h4>John Doe</h4>
                    <p>Rating: <span class="fa fa-star checked"></span><span class="fa fa-star checked"></span><span
                            class="fa fa-star checked"></span><span class="fa fa-star checked"></span><span
                            class="fa fa-star"></span></p>
                    <p>Reviewed on: January 28, 2020</p>
                    <p>There is an incredible amount of errors for a simple design like this.
                        1. The rubber feet are NON-Stick meaning I’m now trying to glue them to the board.
                        2. The rubber feet are too short and the voltage terminals are longer, resulting in the rubber
                        feet being
                        pointless. I’m now adding washers to fix this issue.

                        I cannot comment on the board quality as I’ve now had to put off testing to fix stupid design
                        flaws.

                        I recommend going with another brand and spending the extra buck or two.</p>
                </div>
            </div>


            <div class="card mb-4 border-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <h4>Joe Smith</h4>
                    <p>Rating: <span class="fa fa-star checked"></span><span class="fa fa-star "></span><span
                            class="fa fa-star"></span><span class="fa fa-star"></span><span class="fa fa-star"></span>
                    <p>Reviewed on: January 20, 2020</p>
                    <p>I hated it so much, No one should buy this</p>
                </div>

            </div>

        </div>
</body>
